26:01.106 --> 26:02.186
college isn't for everyone.

26:02.352 --> 26:03.478
Neither is marriage.

26:04.937 --> 26:06.607
I can't believe she told you.

26:06.773 --> 26:09.234
I can't believe you didn't.
We're supposed to be brothers.

26:09.400 --> 26:10.807
Look, I didn't want to put you in

26:10.932 --> 26:11.875
an awkward position with Burt, okay?

26:12.000 --> 26:13.363
I don't want him to know yet.

26:13.529 --> 26:14.445
Hey, you think something

26:14.570 --> 26:16.029
you have to keep
from everyone you love

26:16.154 --> 26:18.118
might not be the best idea in
the first place?

26:18.284 --> 26:20.084
Don't get down on me
about this, dude.

26:20.209 --> 26:21.985
Rachel's, like, the only good
thing I've got going

26:22.110 --> 26:23.207
in my life right now.

26:23.373 --> 26:25.000
No, she isn't, Finn.

26:25.166 --> 26:27.669
Look, I get you've had a rough
year with finding out

26:27.835 --> 26:29.922
who your dad really is and-and
losing the scholarship,

26:30.088 --> 26:33.630
but you're a star, Finn,
just as bright as Rachel.

26:33.755 --> 26:35.177
You just don't believe in yourself.

26:35.343 --> 26:36.967
Yeah, well, the proof's in
the pudding, okay?

26:37.092 --> 26:39.348
And my pudding pretty much sucks.

26:39.514 --> 26:42.189
Look, I'm not telling you that
you shouldn't marry Rachel.

26:42.314 --> 26:43.977
I love her despite all of her crazy,

26:44.143 --> 26:47.064
and I think that you'd be
lucky to marry her... one day.

26:47.230 --> 26:48.946
But I don't want you just to
turn yourself into nothing

26:49.071 --> 26:50.901
but the guy who holds her purse
on the red carpet.

26:51.067 --> 26:52.316
Look, I'm getting to the
point in my life where

26:52.441 --> 26:54.446
I kind of need to be honest with
myself about who I am.

26:54.612 --> 26:55.822
And who is that?

26:55.988 --> 26:57.754
Not you.

26:57.879 --> 27:00.452
Not Rachel.

27:00.618 --> 27:02.659
That's the point, Finn.

27:02.784 --> 27:05.415
There are plenty of us, trust me.

27:05.581 --> 27:09.002
The one thing that Glee Clubs
and theater programs don't have

27:09.168 --> 27:11.964
is the hot, straight football player
who can sing and sort of dance.

27:13.805 --> 27:15.429
You're unique, Finn.

27:15.860 --> 27:17.925
And I can't see this proposal
thing as anything else

27:18.050 --> 27:20.013
but you giving up on yourself.

27:20.179 --> 27:22.470
No, no, it's not.

27:25.057 --> 27:27.020
At least I don't...
I don't think it is.

27:28.585 --> 27:30.335
Your time isn't up, Finn.

27:31.260 --> 27:32.513
It's just beginning.

27:36.351 --> 27:37.851
Hey, Kurt.

27:40.324 --> 27:42.373
Thanks.

27:53.772 --> 27:55.299
Hold it right there, Sandbacks.

27:55.606 --> 27:57.301
You and I need to
have a serious chat.

27:57.608 --> 27:59.318
Now I realize when I chose Becky

27:59.443 --> 28:00.569
as co-captain for the Cheerios!

28:00.694 --> 28:02.097
it might have rubbed
you the wrong way.

28:02.263 --> 28:03.181
Wanky.

28:03.614 --> 28:05.273
And I've often admired
the craven heartlessness

28:05.398 --> 28:07.686
of your pointless,
vindictive back-stabbing.

28:08.001 --> 28:10.045
Kind of takes me back
to the old salad days.

28:10.170 --> 28:11.982
But you crossed the Maginot Line

28:12.148 --> 28:13.900
when you started messing with
Sue Sylvester's family.

28:14.066 --> 28:16.028
What are you talking about?
What family?

28:16.194 --> 28:18.322
You lodged a complaint
about my teaching tactics

28:18.488 --> 28:20.490
with Principal Figgins,
possibly derailing my bid

28:20.747 --> 28:23.493
for tenure just when I'm trying
to have a baby!

28:23.717 --> 28:26.371
A baby? With whose vagina?

28:26.603 --> 28:28.040
Hey, what is going on here?

28:28.305 --> 28:30.649
Coach Sylvester is accusing me
of something I didn't do.

28:30.774 --> 28:33.101
Oh, stop with the lies, sweater
meat, or you will be hawking

28:33.226 --> 28:34.921
nude glossies of yourself behind
the Dumpster of Hooters

28:35.087 --> 28:36.173
by the weekend.

28:36.396 --> 28:37.406
I know you did this!

28:37.531 --> 28:38.743
Sue, enough!

28:39.035 --> 28:41.386
No one messes with my family.
No one.

28:42.869 --> 28:44.947
Oh, and you can rest your fetid,
woolly head, William.

28:45.072 --> 28:46.815
I don't need your baby spunk anymore.

28:46.940 --> 28:49.668
Got myself another donor.
And a much better one.

28:49.793 --> 28:51.243
Who?

29:05.291 --> 29:07.329
I just got my new pamphlets
back from the printer.

29:07.644 --> 29:11.223
I am feeling so Stephen King
with these things lately.

29:11.348 --> 29:13.275
You know, just so prolific.

29:13.400 --> 29:14.943
That's great, Em, but I really need

29:15.068 --> 29:16.895
to translate this song
for my big number tomorrow.

29:17.020 --> 29:19.091
It's my last chance to wow
the kids with my español.

29:19.439 --> 29:20.884
By the end of the week, I need

29:21.141 --> 29:22.651
every single one of those kids
begging Figgins

29:22.776 --> 29:24.903
to give me that tenure spot.

29:25.028 --> 29:27.155
<i>Conversación.</i>
Of course.

29:27.280 --> 29:29.658
"Conversation" in Spanish is
<i>conversación.</i>

29:35.565 --> 29:37.609
Do you realize how important
this tenure is for us,

29:37.841 --> 29:39.051
if we want to start a family?

29:39.176 --> 29:41.053
It means we will
always be able to feed our kids,

29:41.178 --> 29:43.323
get them health insurance.

29:46.049 --> 29:47.559
Emma, enough!

29:47.684 --> 29:51.003
Can't you see I'm doing
this to take care of you?

29:52.672 --> 29:55.752
Okay, I think I can
take care of myself.

29:55.918 --> 29:57.921
You know what, I'm sorry.

29:58.178 --> 29:59.855
I just wanted to show
you my new pamphlets.

29:59.980 --> 30:01.239
I'm really proud of them.

30:01.364 --> 30:04.219
They're silly, Emma.
I'm sorry, I love you,

30:04.517 --> 30:06.495
but do you really think
the kids take them seriously?

30:06.620 --> 30:07.440
Okay, you know what?

30:07.565 --> 30:09.581
I know that the titles are silly;
that's the point.

30:09.706 --> 30:11.950
Sometimes you have to
be a little provocative

30:12.075 --> 30:14.002
if you want to get
teenagers' attention.

30:14.127 --> 30:15.772
They're <i>conversación</i> starters.

30:15.938 --> 30:17.482
And you're being really mean.

30:17.714 --> 30:19.614
You got a pamphlet for that?

30:20.584 --> 30:22.279
Emma, I'm sorry.

30:22.502 --> 30:23.738
Emma, wait.

30:32.579 --> 30:34.761
<i>Como puede ser verdad?</i>

30:36.366 --> 30:40.422
<i>Last night I dreamt of San Pedro</i>

30:40.671 --> 30:44.593
<i>Just like I'd never gone,
I knew the song</i>

30:44.841 --> 30:49.421
<i>A young girl with eyes
like the desert</i>

30:49.546 --> 30:53.105
<i>It all seems like yesterday,
not far away</i>

30:53.809 --> 30:55.312
<i>Tropical the island breeze</i>

30:55.478 --> 30:57.763
<i>All of nature wild and free</i>

30:57.888 --> 30:59.191
<i>This is where I long to be</i>

30:59.357 --> 31:01.483
<i>La isla bonita</i>

31:01.608 --> 31:04.154
<i>And when the samba played</i>

31:04.320 --> 31:05.614
<i>The sun would set so high</i>

31:05.780 --> 31:08.158
<i>Ring through my ears
