<i>Satisfy me, baby</i>

35:03.100 --> 35:05.687
<i>Menos conversación y mas
accion, por favor</i>

35:05.853 --> 35:07.230
<i>Hey! Muchas gracias.</i>

35:12.818 --> 35:14.404
It was you.

35:14.570 --> 35:16.364
You're the one who complained
to Principal Figgins about me.

35:16.530 --> 35:18.908
Yeah, and I'd do it all over
again after that performance.

35:19.074 --> 35:20.627
You're messing with
adult things here, Santana.

35:20.752 --> 35:22.954
This is my job.
This is my life.

35:23.120 --> 35:25.632
And this is my education,
and it's not a joke to me,

35:25.757 --> 35:27.459
although it seems to be one to you.

35:27.625 --> 35:29.711
What are you talking about?
They all loved my performance.

35:29.877 --> 35:31.155
Because they don't know any better.

35:31.280 --> 35:33.339
It's your fault.
You're their teacher.

35:33.505 --> 35:36.717
You went from "La Cucaracha"
to a bullfighting mariachi.

35:36.842 --> 35:40.054
Why don't you just dress up
as the Taco Bell Chihuahua

35:40.220 --> 35:42.223
and bark the theme song
to <i>Dora the Explorer</i> ?<

35:42.389 --> 35:44.434
You don't even know enough
to be embarrassed

35:44.600 --> 35:46.936
about these stereotypes
that you're perpetuating.

35:47.102 --> 35:48.354
That's not fair.
Isn't it?

35:48.520 --> 35:51.399
What did you want to be
when you grew up?

35:51.565 --> 35:53.668
Why did you become
a Spanish teacher, Mr. Shue?

35:57.163 --> 35:58.164
Because...

36:03.196 --> 36:06.481
it was the only teaching
position open at the time.

36:08.800 --> 36:11.645
I want to remind you
of something that

36:11.770 --> 36:14.005
an amazing teacher once taught me:

36:14.171 --> 36:17.465
without passion, you can't succeed.

36:18.694 --> 36:19.994
Who taught you that?

36:20.344 --> 36:21.989
You did.

36:22.114 --> 36:23.457
And you do.

36:23.582 --> 36:24.933
When you teach Glee.

36:29.103 --> 36:31.873
I'm telling you,
there's no word but "genius."

36:32.107 --> 36:33.733
I wouldn't call it that.

36:33.899 --> 36:35.360
What's genius?
My plan for Regionals?

36:35.526 --> 36:38.363
No. Your lil'punkin's pamphlets.

36:39.697 --> 36:40.782
"Taint Misbehavin'."

36:40.948 --> 36:41.709
Mm-hmm.

36:41.834 --> 36:43.026
It's all about the importance

36:43.151 --> 36:44.577
of thoroughly washing your jockstrap.

36:44.743 --> 36:46.162
Hey, bub,

36:46.328 --> 36:48.289
MRSA bacteria infection
is no laughing matter.

36:48.455 --> 36:49.415
No matter how much I talked

36:49.675 --> 36:52.710
to my guys about
the steamy lurking dangers,

36:52.876 --> 36:53.753
nobody cared

36:54.012 --> 36:56.005
Until Emma found a way
to get through to them.

36:56.171 --> 36:57.925
Come on, guys!

36:58.050 --> 37:01.095
Why, just last week,
three Fort Wayne gymnasts

37:01.220 --> 37:03.547
had to have their junk amputated!

37:03.672 --> 37:06.183
I stopped washing down there
'cause it seemed kind of gay.

37:06.308 --> 37:08.518
I thought that's what the hair
catching the dirt.

37:09.027 --> 37:10.688
Huh. Lift and scrub.

37:10.813 --> 37:12.146
Who knew it was so easy?

37:12.447 --> 37:14.232
And now their kibbles and bits are

37:14.449 --> 37:15.942
as clean as a little angel's tear.

37:16.108 --> 37:18.061
And when I showed that to my Cooter,

37:18.186 --> 37:21.948
not only did he order
10,000 copies for Ohio State,

37:22.114 --> 37:25.285
he got every team in the Big Ten
to order copies, too.

37:25.451 --> 37:27.495
- Wow, that's...
- It's genius!

37:27.661 --> 37:29.998
I have never met a
teacher whose passion

37:30.164 --> 37:31.833
literally saves lives.

37:31.999 --> 37:33.376
Aren't you proud of her, Will?

37:34.752 --> 37:36.280
Yes.

37:36.405 --> 37:37.338
Absolutely.

37:38.922 --> 37:40.383
Genius! You!

37:40.549 --> 37:41.550
Stop.

37:44.680 --> 37:47.223
{pub}And the award for Best Conjugator
goes to

37:47.389 --> 37:48.393
Señora Stephanie.

37:50.887 --> 37:53.531
Thank you, Señor Martinez.

37:53.656 --> 37:55.734
And thanks to you, Claudia knows now

37:55.859 --> 37:57.935
to go before she comes to work.

37:59.693 --> 38:02.071
Now finally, Most Improved:

38:02.237 --> 38:04.542
Will Schuester.

38:04.667 --> 38:06.044
- Wow.
- Come on, man!

38:06.169 --> 38:07.744
Thanks.

38:07.910 --> 38:09.542
Wow, I...

38:09.667 --> 38:10.455
Oh.

38:10.707 --> 38:11.666
<i>Fue un año maravilloso.</i>

38:11.791 --> 38:12.999
It was a beautiful year, everyone.

38:13.259 --> 38:14.417
<i>Gracias.
Hey, de nada.</i>

38:14.677 --> 38:16.461
<i>Gracias.</i>

38:16.679 --> 38:18.840
Your teeth are like
fresh-driven snow white.

38:18.965 --> 38:20.506
Like Larry Bird white.

38:22.552 --> 38:24.093
Most Improved.

38:24.259 --> 38:27.055
I don't think that's the award
a Spanish teacher wants to get

38:27.221 --> 38:28.466
in Spanish class.

38:28.591 --> 38:31.486
Will, man, you work hard,
you take care of your kids.

38:31.611 --> 38:33.102
They're very lucky to have you, man.

38:33.268 --> 38:34.939
They deserve better.

38:35.064 --> 38:36.147
They deserve you.

38:36.313 --> 38:38.650
Oh, so when do I start?

38:38.816 --> 38:40.568
How about Monday?

38:40.734 --> 38:41.979
I spoke to Figgins.

38:42.104 --> 38:44.315
I had all the kids go in
and talk to him, as well.

38:44.440 --> 38:47.075
They all want to take Spanish
if you're the teacher.

38:47.241 --> 38:49.011
What, he's offering me a job?

38:51.280 --> 38:52.290
Teaching?

38:52.415 --> 38:53.623
During the day?

38:53.789 --> 38:56.350
I hope you're not a vampire.

38:56.959 --> 38:58.461
Oh, man.

38:59.503 --> 39:01.255
Okay.

39:01.421 --> 39:03.883
Oh, man, you don...
you don't understand.

39:04.049 --> 39:05.551
My-My parents,

39:05.717 --> 39:07.439
my parents were immigrants.

39:07.564 --> 39:10.275
And they had to lie
about their citizenship

39:10.400 --> 39:12.227
to go to high school.

39:12.352 --> 39:14.529
And now I'm teaching it.

39:14.654 --> 39:16.187
It's the American Dream, right?

39:16.406 --> 39:17.689
Yeah.

39:17.855 --> 39:19.451
But what about you?

39:19.576 --> 39:22.754
Oh, there's-there's an opening
in the History department.

39:22.879 --> 39:24.278
I've always loved history.

39:24.444 --> 39:26.114
Well, the History Channel, at least.

39:26.280 --> 39:28.533
- Right.
- Maybe I'll find my duende there.

39:28.699 --> 39:31.496
No, I've seen you, I've seen you
teach Glee Club, man.

39:31.621 --> 39:33.830
You have <i>duende</i>
coming out of your <i>orejas</i>.

39:34.955 --> 39:36.416
- Ears.
- Ears, right.

39:36.582 --> 39:37.702
I got you.

39:37.827 --> 39:38.876
Thank you so much.

39:39.042 --> 39:41.372
Thank you.

39:41.497 --> 39:44.507
So, wait a minute, who ended up
getting the tenure position?

39:48.844 --> 39:50.715
Thank you, Becky.

39:50.840 --> 39:53.985
My online pharmacist
has recommended these

39:54.110 --> 39:56.438
fertility injections every day,
twice a day,

39:56.563 --> 39:59.355
until Little Susie
or Little Sylvester catches.

39:59.521 --> 40:00.398
You down with that?

40:00.564 --> 40:01.899
No problem, Coach.

40:04.020 --> 40:05.194
What's wrong?

40:05.360 --> 40:07.488
Coach, I have a confession to make.

40:07.654 --> 40:09.117
Take a seat.

40:09.242 --> 40:10.533
Now, if this is about

40:10.699 --> 40:13.972
the complaint you lodged against
me with Principal Figgins,

40:14.097 --> 40:15.371
I already know.

40:15.537 --> 40:16.456
You do, Coach?

40:16.622 --> 40:17.692
Oh, Becky, I've known

40:17.817 --> 40:19.294
ever since
I tinker-tailor-soldier-spied

40:19.419 --> 40:21.419
my way into Figgins's
file cabinet and read

40:21.585 --> 40:22.462
the evaluation cards.

40:22.628 --> 40:23.681
And when I saw one

40:23.806 --> 40:25.150
written in crayon,
I knew it was either

40:25.275 --> 40:27.425
you or Brittany,
and you're the better speller.

40:27.591 --> 40:28.553
Coach, I'm sorry.

40:28.678 --> 40:30.094
I was just looking out for the team.

40:30.260 --> 40:33.691
Did you mean what you wrote?

40:33.816 --> 40:36.184
That you're worried I'm not
as focused on the Cheerios!

40:36.350 --> 40:37.769
as I used to be?

40:37.935 --> 40:39.397
Well, then you don't need be sorry.

40:39.522 --> 40:41.773
And thank you for the feedback.

40:41.939 --> 40:43.191
You're not mad?

40:43.357 --> 40:44.692
No, Becky.

40:46.195 --> 40:49.822
But impending motherhood
doth given me perspective.

40:49.988 --> 40:53.701
Oh, Becky, I'm reminded
winning,

40:53.867 --> 40:54.994
my girls,

40:55.160 --> 40:56.798
destroying my enemies.

40:56.923 --> 40:58.466
Motherhood's not gonna change that.

40:58.591 --> 41:01.209
If anything, it makes me
want them far more.

41:01.375 --> 41:03.922
You're an excellent
co-captain, Becky.

41:04.047 --> 41:05.713
You're like me.

41:05.879 --> 41:07.509
Not afraid to make the tough calls.

41:07.634 --> 41:08.883
Coach?

41:09.049 --> 41:10.949
You're gonna be a great mom.

41:37.953 --> 41:39.874
There you are, baby.
You ready?

41:39.999 --> 41:41.874
For lunch.

41:42.040 --> 41:43.251
We're going off-campus, right?

41:43.417 --> 41:44.919
Hey, Sam.

42:05.191 --> 42:06.607
What's all this?

42:11.781 --> 42:15.617
"So You Were A Jerk To Your Fiance."

42:17.286 --> 42:20.746
Not particularly clever,
but I appreciate your pith.

42:23.062 --> 42:25.710
"Congratulations... I Love You."

42:25.876 --> 42:27.211
These are wonderful.

42:27.377 --> 42:28.590
They're wonderful.

42:30.166 --> 42:33.217
A little myopic maybe,
but a great first effort.

42:37.056 --> 42:38.431
I'm so proud of you.

42:38.674 --> 42:41.519
So do I call you Professor
or Madam or what?

42:41.644 --> 42:43.237
I'm not sure of the protocol here.

42:43.362 --> 42:44.522
No, no, no, it's just tenure.

42:44.647 --> 42:45.773
You can call me Emma.

42:45.898 --> 42:48.232
Or sweetheart
or cutie pie or doll-face.

42:48.398 --> 42:49.393
- Or Professor Doll-Face.
- Ooh.

42:49.518 --> 42:50.495
I like Professor Doll-Face.

42:54.190 --> 42:56.157
My first marriage didn't
work out because my wife

42:56.323 --> 42:57.366
didn't believe in me.

42:57.532 --> 43:01.287
And then I go and pull
the same crap on you.

43:01.453 --> 43:05.259
All I know is that right now,
in this moment,

43:05.384 --> 43:08.880
I just want it to stop.

43:09.005 --> 43:13.132
I want to sit here, eat
some chicken and look back on

43:13.298 --> 43:15.218
everything you've done
to get to this moment

43:15.384 --> 43:19.256
and everything I'm going to do
from this moment on

43:19.381 --> 43:23.851
to make sure you feel...
as special... and amazing

43:24.017 --> 43:26.655
as I know you are.

